# 09 — Protocol Standard

## DriveCore Protocol (DCP) v0.1

Authoritative spec: `docs/004_Communication_Protocol.md`.

## CAN FD Gen1

- One bus, linear topology, 500 kbit/s nominal, 2 Mbit/s data.
- Nodes: DCC `0x10`, ECU `0x20`, Button Box `0x30`.
- ID layout: Message Class + Device Type + Instance.
- No new CAN IDs without updating protocol source of truth.

## Message requirements

Each message shall define (in spec): sender, scope, rate/timeout, payload layout, scaling, version, stale handling.

## DCPI (STM32 ↔ ESP32)

- Binary, versioned, CRC — see `docs/004` §4, `firmware/shared/include/drivecore/dcpi.h`.
- **JSON not on SPI.** ESP32 translates to JSON for REST/WebSocket only.

## REST / WebSocket

Authoritative UI contract: `docs/006`. Base `/api/v1/`, telemetry WebSocket 20 Hz.

## Heartbeat

Presence ≠ full health. States: BOOT, INIT, RUN, DEGRADED, FAULT, LOST (per `docs/004`).

## Single source of truth

Protocol constants in `firmware/shared/`. Future: codegen from `.dcmsg` (roadmap — not implemented).

EDL-008 (one bus), EDL-009 (DCP), EDL-010 (binary SPI).
